<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Order Submitted - secondhandcell</title>
    
    <!-- IMMEDIATE ACCESS CONTROL CHECK (MUST RUN FIRST) -->
    <script>
        const expectedPathSegment = '/sell/';
        const referrer = document.referrer;
        const homepageUrl = 'https://secondhandcell.com/index.html';

        // If the referrer is empty (direct access) or doesn't contain the expected path, redirect immediately.
        if (!referrer || !referrer.includes(expectedPathSegment)) {
            // Redirect immediately, preventing the browser from loading subsequent scripts (including analytics).
            window.location.replace(homepageUrl);
            // Stop further script execution
            throw new Error("Unauthorized access attempt redirected."); 
        }
    </script>
    <!-- END IMMEDIATE ACCESS CONTROL CHECK -->

    <!-- AUTHORIZED ANALYTICS SCRIPTS (ONLY RUNS IF ACCESS CHECK PASSES) -->
    <!-- Google Tag Manager -->
    <script>(function(w,d,s,l,i){w[l]=w[l]||[];w[l].push({'gtm.start':
    new Date().getTime(),event:'gtm.js'});var f=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],
    j=d.createElement(s),dl=l!='dataLayer'?'&l='+l:'';j.async=true;j.src=
    'https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtm.js?id='+i+dl;f.parentNode.insertBefore(j,f);
    })(window,document,'script','dataLayer','GTM-W3BM2JC8');</script>
    <!-- End Google Tag Manager -->

    <!-- Google Global Site Tag (gtag.js) and Conversion Event -->
    <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=AW-17534255111"></script>
    <script>
        window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
        function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}
        gtag('js', new Date());
    
        gtag('config', 'AW-17534255111');
        gtag('config', 'G-8JYPJDKSP8');
    
        gtag('event', 'conversion', {'send_to': 'AW-17534255111/09vcCOjI85QbEIeA_qhB'});
    </script>
    <!-- END AUTHORIZED ANALYTICS SCRIPTS -->
    
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.5.2/css/brands.min.css" crossorigin="anonymous" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" />
        
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
            -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
        }
    </style>
    
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/site-chrome.css">
</head>
            // NOTE: The Access Control Check was moved to the <head> for immediate execution.
            // This script now only handles content loading once the page is confirmed accessible.

            const shippingInstruction = document.getElementById('shippingInstruction');
            const emailOptionCard = document.getElementById('emailOptionCard');
            const kitOptionCard = document.getElementById('kitOptionCard');
            const emailOptionTag = document.getElementById('emailOptionTag');
            const kitOptionTag = document.getElementById('kitOptionTag');
            const summaryPromoRow = document.getElementById('summaryPromoRow');
            const summaryPromoValue = document.getElementById('summaryPromoValue');
            const promoConfirmationCard = document.getElementById('promoConfirmationCard');
            const emailLabelCard = document.getElementById('emailLabelCard');
            const labelStatusMessage = document.getElementById('labelStatusMessage');
            const labelDownloadLink = document.getElementById('labelDownloadLink');
            const labelTrackingDisplay = document.getElementById('labelTrackingDisplay');
            const copyLabelLinkButton = document.getElementById('copyLabelLinkButton');
            const urlParams = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);

            let sessionSummary = null;
            try {
                const stored = sessionStorage.getItem('shcOrderSummary');
                if (stored) {
                    sessionSummary = JSON.parse(stored);
                    sessionStorage.removeItem('shcOrderSummary');
                }
            } catch (error) {
                console.warn('Unable to read stored order summary:', error);
            }

            const coalesceValue = (key) => {
                const paramValue = urlParams.get(key);
                if (paramValue !== null && paramValue !== undefined && paramValue.toString().trim() !== '') {
                    return paramValue;
                }
                if (sessionSummary && sessionSummary[key] !== undefined && sessionSummary[key] !== null) {
                    return String(sessionSummary[key]);
                }
                return '';
            };

            const coalesceNumber = (...keys) => {
                for (const key of keys) {
                    if (!key) continue;
                    const value = coalesceValue(key);
                    if (value === '') continue;
                    const numeric = Number(value);
                    if (Number.isFinite(numeric)) {
                        return numeric;
                    }
                }
                return null;
            };

            const formatDisplayText = (value) => {
                if (!value) return '';
                return value
                    .toString()
                    .replace(/[_-]+/g, ' ')
                    .replace(/\s+/g, ' ')
                    .trim()
                    .replace(/\b\w/g, (char) => char.toUpperCase());
            };

            const heroNameEl = document.getElementById('heroName');
            const heroPriceEl = document.getElementById('heroPrice');
            const heroDeviceEl = document.getElementById('heroDevice');
            const summaryOrderIdEl = document.getElementById('summaryOrderId');
            const summaryNameEl = document.getElementById('summaryName');
            const summaryDeviceEl = document.getElementById('summaryDevice');
            const summaryPriceEl = document.getElementById('summaryPrice');
            const summaryPaymentMethodEl = document.getElementById('summaryPaymentMethod');

            const resetCardState = () => {
                if (emailOptionCard) {
                    emailOptionCard.classList.remove('ring-2', 'ring-emerald-400', 'shadow-lg', 'bg-white');
                }
                if (kitOptionCard) {
                    kitOptionCard.classList.remove('ring-2', 'ring-indigo-400', 'shadow-lg', 'bg-white');
                }
                if (emailOptionTag) emailOptionTag.classList.add('hidden');
                if (kitOptionTag) kitOptionTag.classList.add('hidden');
            };

            const setCardState = (preference) => {
                resetCardState();
                if (preference === 'ship_kit') {
                    if (kitOptionCard) kitOptionCard.classList.add('ring-2', 'ring-indigo-400', 'shadow-lg', 'bg-white');
                    if (kitOptionTag) kitOptionTag.classList.remove('hidden');
                } else {
                    if (emailOptionCard) emailOptionCard.classList.add('ring-2', 'ring-emerald-400', 'shadow-lg', 'bg-white');
                    if (emailOptionTag) emailOptionTag.classList.remove('hidden');
                }
            };

            const SHIPPING_KIT_FEE = 10;
            const storedShippingPreference = sessionSummary?.shippingPreference ? String(sessionSummary.shippingPreference) : '';

            const name = coalesceValue('name').trim();
            const orderId = coalesceValue('orderId').trim();
            const labelDownloadUrl = coalesceValue('labelUrl').trim();
            const labelTrackingNumber = coalesceValue('trackingNumber').trim();
            const promoCodeUsed = coalesceValue('promoCode').trim().toUpperCase();
            const promoBonusNumber = coalesceNumber('promoBonusAmount', 'promo_bonus');

            const shippingParam = urlParams.get('shipping');
            const shippingPreferenceSource = coalesceValue('shippingPreference');
            const normalizedShippingPreference = (shippingParam || shippingPreferenceSource || storedShippingPreference || 'email_label').toLowerCase();
            const isShippingKit = normalizedShippingPreference === 'ship_kit';

            const shippingFeeOverride = coalesceNumber('shippingKitFee', 'shipping_fee');
            const originalQuoteNumber = coalesceNumber('originalQuote', 'original_quote', 'originalQuoteValue', 'quote');
            const rawFinalCandidate = coalesceNumber('finalPayout', 'final_payout', 'totalPayout', 'total_payout', 'price');

            const appliedShippingFee = Number.isFinite(shippingFeeOverride) ? shippingFeeOverride : SHIPPING_KIT_FEE;
            const promoBonusValue = Number.isFinite(promoBonusNumber) ? promoBonusNumber : 0;
            const netOriginalQuote = Number.isFinite(originalQuoteNumber)
                ? Math.max(originalQuoteNumber - (isShippingKit ? appliedShippingFee : 0), 0)
                : null;

            let finalPayoutNumber = Number.isFinite(rawFinalCandidate) ? rawFinalCandidate : null;

            if (Number.isFinite(netOriginalQuote)) {
                const expectedFinalWithPromo = Math.max(netOriginalQuote + promoBonusValue, 0);
                const missingOrIncorrectFinal =
                    !Number.isFinite(finalPayoutNumber) ||
                    (isShippingKit && Math.abs(finalPayoutNumber - expectedFinalWithPromo) > 0.01) ||
                    (promoBonusValue > 0 && Number.isFinite(finalPayoutNumber) && Math.abs(finalPayoutNumber - netOriginalQuote) <= 0.01);

                if (missingOrIncorrectFinal) {
                    finalPayoutNumber = expectedFinalWithPromo;
                }
            }

            if (!Number.isFinite(finalPayoutNumber) && Number.isFinite(originalQuoteNumber)) {
                const originalWithPromo = Math.max(originalQuoteNumber + promoBonusValue, 0);
                finalPayoutNumber = originalWithPromo;
            }

            if (!Number.isFinite(finalPayoutNumber)) {
                finalPayoutNumber = 0;
            }

            const formattedPrice = finalPayoutNumber.toLocaleString('en-US', { style: 'currency', currency: 'USD' });

            const deviceParts = [];
            const deviceName = coalesceValue('device').trim();
            if (deviceName) deviceParts.push(deviceName);
            const storage = coalesceValue('storage').trim();
            if (storage) deviceParts.push(storage);
            const carrier = coalesceValue('carrier').trim();
            if (carrier) deviceParts.push(formatDisplayText(carrier));
            const deviceSummary = deviceParts.length ? deviceParts.join('  ') : 'Device details on file';

            const paymentMethod = coalesceValue('paymentMethod').trim();
            const paymentSummary = paymentMethod ? formatDisplayText(paymentMethod) : 'Not specified';

            heroNameEl.textContent = name || 'Friend';
            heroPriceEl.textContent = formattedPrice;
            heroDeviceEl.textContent = deviceSummary;
            summaryOrderIdEl.textContent = orderId || 'Pending';
            summaryNameEl.textContent = name || 'Your Name';
            summaryDeviceEl.textContent = deviceSummary;
            summaryPriceEl.textContent = formattedPrice;
            summaryPaymentMethodEl.textContent = paymentSummary;

            if (Number.isFinite(promoBonusNumber) && promoBonusNumber > 0 && summaryPromoRow && summaryPromoValue) {
                summaryPromoRow.classList.remove('hidden');
                const promoSuffix = promoCodeUsed ? ` (${promoCodeUsed})` : '';
                summaryPromoValue.textContent = `+$${promoBonusNumber.toFixed(2)}${promoSuffix}`;
                if (promoConfirmationCard) {
                    promoConfirmationCard.classList.remove('hidden');
                }
            }

            const promoReminder = promoBonusNumber ? ' Ship within 48 hours to keep your $10 Ship48 bonus.' : '';

            if (normalizedShippingPreference === 'ship_kit') {
                setCardState('ship_kit');
                shippingInstruction.innerHTML = `
                    <div>
                        <strong>Shipping Kit Instructions:</strong>
                        <div class="mt-2 space-y-2">
                            <p class="text-slate-700">We're mailing you a padded kit with an adhesive strip and prepaid label. Expect tracking shortly.</p>
                            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-1 text-slate-700">
                                <li>When it arrives, place your device in the protective sleeve and add any padding provided.</li>
                                <li>Include the enclosed device ID sticker or a note with your order number inside the mailer.</li>
                                <li>Seal the mailer tightly, attach the prepaid label, and drop at any USPS location.</li>
                            </ol>
                            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Keep your USPS receipt for tracking. Need help? Reply to our confirmation email.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                `;
            } else {
                setCardState('email_label');
                const labelStatusText = labelDownloadUrl
                    ? 'Your prepaid USPS label is ready below and has been sent to your inbox.'
                    : "We're generating your prepaid USPS label now and will email it shortly.";

                shippingInstruction.innerHTML = `
                    <div>
                        <strong>Email Label Instructions:</strong>
                        <div class="mt-2 space-y-2">
                            <p class="text-slate-700">${labelStatusText}${promoReminder}</p>
                            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-1 text-slate-700">
                                <li>Print the label and grab a sturdy box with padding (bubble wrap or soft cloth).</li>
                                <li>Power off the device, remove SIM/eSIM, and add a note with your order number inside.</li>
                                <li>Seal every edge with tape, place the label flat on the box, and drop at USPS.</li>
                            </ol>
                            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Tip: snap a photo of the sealed box and receipt to track your drop-off.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                `;
            }

            if (normalizedShippingPreference === 'email_label' && labelDownloadUrl && emailLabelCard && labelDownloadLink) {
                emailLabelCard.classList.remove('hidden');
                labelDownloadLink.href = labelDownloadUrl;
                if (labelStatusMessage) {
                    labelStatusMessage.textContent = promoBonusNumber
                        ? 'Download your label and ship within 48 hours to keep your $10 bonus.'
                        : 'Download your label and ship within 48 hours to lock in your payout.';
                }
                if (labelTrackingNumber && labelTrackingDisplay) {
                    const trackingHref = `https://tools.usps.com/go/TrackConfirmAction?qtc_tLabels1=${encodeURIComponent(labelTrackingNumber)}`;
                    labelTrackingDisplay.innerHTML = `Tracking number: <a href="${trackingHref}" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-emerald-800 underline">${labelTrackingNumber}</a>`;
                } else if (labelTrackingDisplay) {
                    labelTrackingDisplay.textContent = '';
                }
                if (copyLabelLinkButton) {
                    copyLabelLinkButton.addEventListener('click', async () => {
                        try {
                            await navigator.clipboard.writeText(labelDownloadUrl);
                            if (labelStatusMessage) {
                                labelStatusMessage.textContent = 'Label link copied!';
                            }
                        } catch (error) {
                            const tempInput = document.createElement('input');
                            tempInput.value = labelDownloadUrl;
                            document.body.appendChild(tempInput);
                            tempInput.select();
                            try {
                                document.execCommand('copy');
                                if (labelStatusMessage) {
                                    labelStatusMessage.textContent = 'Label link copied!';
                                }
                            } catch (fallbackError) {
                                if (labelStatusMessage) {
                                    labelStatusMessage.textContent = 'Copy failedplease copy the link from the button.';
                                }
                            }
                            tempInput.remove();
                        }
                    });
                }
            }

            const transactionId = orderId;
            const basketTotal = Number.isFinite(finalPayoutNumber) ? finalPayoutNumber : null;

            // Tracking pixel for affiliate conversion
            if (transactionId && transactionId !== 'unknown' && basketTotal && basketTotal > 0) {
                const trackingPixel = document.createElement('iframe');
                trackingPixel.src = `https://scdcb.com/p.ashx?a=144&e=305&t=${encodeURIComponent(transactionId)}&p=${basketTotal.toFixed(2)}`;
                trackingPixel.height = '1';
                trackingPixel.width = '1';
                trackingPixel.frameBorder = '0';
                trackingPixel.style.display = 'none';
                document.body.appendChild(trackingPixel);
                console.log('Tracking pixel loaded:', trackingPixel.src);
            } else {
                console.warn('Tracking pixel not loaded: Missing transaction ID or basket total');
            }
        });
    </script>


  <script src="/assets/js/page-tracker.js" defer></script>
  <script>
    (function () {
      const CONVERSION_LABEL = 'order-submitted';
      let recorded = false;

      const attemptRecord = () => {
        if (recorded || !window.PageTracker || typeof window.PageTracker.recordConversion !== 'function') {
          return recorded;
        }
        const success = window.PageTracker.recordConversion({
          path: window.location.pathname || '/order-submitted',
          label: CONVERSION_LABEL,
          title: document.title || '',
          metadata: {
            query: window.location.search || '',
            type: 'order-confirmation',
          },
        });
        if (success) {
          recorded = true;
        }
        return success;
      };

      if (!attemptRecord()) {
        let attempts = 0;
        const maxAttempts = 40;
        const retryInterval = setInterval(() => {
          attempts += 1;
          if (attemptRecord() || attempts >= maxAttempts) {
            clearInterval(retryInterval);
          }
        }, 250);

        const handler = () => {
          if (attemptRecord()) {
            window.removeEventListener('page-tracker:updated', handler);
          }
        };

        window.addEventListener('page-tracker:ready', handler, { once: true });
        window.addEventListener('page-tracker:updated', handler);
      }
    })();
  </script>

  <script defer src="/assets/js/cookie-consent.js"></script>
  <script type="module" src="/assets/js/global-auth.js" defer></script>
</body>
</html>

/workspaces/BuyBacking/apps/web/node_modules/tp-events/dist/docs/index.html
-------------------------------
<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
	<title>tp-events | tp-events</title>
	<meta name="description" content="">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
	<style type="text/css">/*! normalize.css v1.1.3 | MIT License | git.io/normalize */
/* ========================================================================== HTML5 display definitions ========================================================================== */
/** Correct `block` display not defined in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. */
article, aside, details, figcaption, figure, footer, header, hgroup, main, nav, section, summary { display: block; }

/** Correct `inline-block` display not defined in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. */
audio, canvas, video { display: inline-block; *display: inline; *zoom: 1; }

/** Prevent modern browsers from displaying `audio` without controls. Remove excess height in iOS 5 devices. */
audio:not([controls]) { display: none; height: 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 7/8/9, Firefox 3, and Safari 4. Known issue: no IE 6 support. */
[hidden] { display: none; }

/* ========================================================================== Base ========================================================================== */
/** 1. Correct text resizing oddly in IE 6/7 when body `font-size` is set using `em` units. 2. Prevent iOS text size adjust after orientation change, without disabling user zoom. */
html { font-size: 100%; /* 1 */ -ms-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* 2 */ -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* 2 */ font-family: sans-serif; }

/** Address `font-family` inconsistency between `textarea` and other form elements. */
button, input, select, textarea { font-family: sans-serif; }

/** Address margins handled incorrectly in IE 6/7. */
body { margin: 0; }

/* ========================================================================== Links ========================================================================== */
/** Address `outline` inconsistency between Chrome and other browsers. */
a:focus { outline: thin dotted; }
a:active, a:hover { outline: 0; }

/** Improve readability when focused and also mouse hovered in all browsers. */
/* ========================================================================== Typography ========================================================================== */
/** Address font sizes and margins set differently in IE 6/7. Address font sizes within `section` and `article` in Firefox 4+, Safari 5, and Chrome. */
h1 { font-size: 2em; margin: 0.67em 0; }

h2 { font-size: 1.5em; margin: 0.83em 0; }

h3 { font-size: 1.17em; margin: 1em 0; }

h4, .tsd-index-panel h3 { font-size: 1em; margin: 1.33em 0; }

h5 { font-size: 0.83em; margin: 1.67em 0; }

h6 { font-size: 0.67em; margin: 2.33em 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 7/8/9, Safari 5, and Chrome. */
abbr[title] { border-bottom: 1px dotted; }

/** Address style set to `bolder` in Firefox 3+, Safari 4/5, and Chrome. */
b, strong { font-weight: bold; }

blockquote { margin: 1em 40px; }

/** Address styling not present in Safari 5 and Chrome. */
dfn { font-style: italic; }

/** Address differences between Firefox and other browsers. Known issue: no IE 6/7 normalization. */
hr { box-sizing: content-box; height: 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 6/7/8/9. */
mark { background: #ff0; color: #000; }

/** Address margins set differently in IE 6/7. */
p, pre { margin: 1em 0; }

/** Correct font family set oddly in IE 6, Safari 4/5, and Chrome. */
code, kbd, pre, samp { font-family: monospace, serif; _font-family: "courier new", monospace; font-size: 1em; }

/** Improve readability of pre-formatted text in all browsers. */
pre { white-space: pre; white-space: pre-wrap; word-wrap: break-word; }

/** Address CSS quotes not supported in IE 6/7. */
q { quotes: none; }
q:before, q:after { content: ""; content: none; }

/** Address `quotes` property not supported in Safari 4. */
/** Address inconsistent and variable font size in all browsers. */
small { font-size: 80%; }

/** Prevent `sub` and `sup` affecting `line-height` in all browsers. */
sub { font-size: 75%; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; }

sup { font-size: 75%; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; }

sub { bottom: -0.25em; }

/* ========================================================================== Lists ========================================================================== */
/** Address margins set differently in IE 6/7. */
dl, menu, ol, ul { margin: 1em 0; }

dd { margin: 0 0 0 40px; }

/** Address paddings set differently in IE 6/7. */
menu, ol, ul { padding: 0 0 0 40px; }

/** Correct list images handled incorrectly in IE 7. */
nav ul, nav ol { list-style: none; list-style-image: none; }

/* ========================================================================== Embedded content ========================================================================== */
/** 1. Remove border when inside `a` element in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. 2. Improve image quality when scaled in IE 7. */
img { border: 0; /* 1 */ -ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; }

/* 2 */
/** Correct overflow displayed oddly in IE 9. */
svg:not(:root) { overflow: hidden; }

/* ========================================================================== Figures ========================================================================== */
/** Address margin not present in IE 6/7/8/9, Safari 5, and Opera 11. */
figure, form { margin: 0; }

/* ========================================================================== Forms ========================================================================== */
/** Correct margin displayed oddly in IE 6/7. */
/** Define consistent border, margin, and padding. */
fieldset { border: 1px solid #c0c0c0; margin: 0 2px; padding: 0.35em 0.625em 0.75em; }

/** 1. Correct color not being inherited in IE 6/7/8/9. 2. Correct text not wrapping in Firefox 3. 3. Correct alignment displayed oddly in IE 6/7. */
legend { border: 0; /* 1 */ padding: 0; white-space: normal; /* 2 */ *margin-left: -7px; }

/* 3 */
/** 1. Correct font size not being inherited in all browsers. 2. Address margins set differently in IE 6/7, Firefox 3+, Safari 5, and Chrome. 3. Improve appearance and consistency in all browsers. */
button, input, select, textarea { font-size: 100%; /* 1 */ margin: 0; /* 2 */ vertical-align: baseline; /* 3 */ *vertical-align: middle; }

/* 3 */
/** Address Firefox 3+ setting `line-height` on `input` using `!important` in the UA stylesheet. */
button, input { line-height: normal; }

/** Address inconsistent `text-transform` inheritance for `button` and `select`. All other form control elements do not inherit `text-transform` values. Correct `button` style inheritance in Chrome, Safari 5+, and IE 6+. Correct `select` style inheritance in Firefox 4+ and Opera. */
button, select { text-transform: none; }

/** 1. Avoid the WebKit bug in Android 4.0.* where (2) destroys native `audio` and `video` controls. 2. Correct inability to style clickable `input` types in iOS. 3. Improve usability and consistency of cursor style between image-type `input` and others. 4. Remove inner spacing in IE 7 without affecting normal text inputs. Known issue: inner spacing remains in IE 6. */
button, html input[type="button"] { -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */ cursor: pointer; /* 3 */ *overflow: visible; }

/* 4 */
input[type="reset"], input[type="submit"] { -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */ cursor: pointer; /* 3 */ *overflow: visible; }

/* 4 */
/** Re-set default cursor for disabled elements. */
button[disabled], html input[disabled] { cursor: default; }

/** 1. Address box sizing set to content-box in IE 8/9. 2. Remove excess padding in IE 8/9. 3. Remove excess padding in IE 7. Known issue: excess padding remains in IE 6. */
input { /* 3 */ }
input[type="checkbox"], input[type="radio"] { box-sizing: border-box; /* 1 */ padding: 0; /* 2 */ *height: 13px; /* 3 */ *width: 13px; }
input[type="search"] { -webkit-appearance: textfield; /* 1 */ /* 2 */ box-sizing: content-box; }
input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-cancel-button, input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-decoration { -webkit-appearance: none; }

/** 1. Address `appearance` set to `searchfield` in Safari 5 and Chrome. 2. Address `box-sizing` set to `border-box` in Safari 5 and Chrome (include `-moz` to future-proof). */
/** Remove inner padding and search cancel button in Safari 5 and Chrome on OS X. */
/** Remove inner padding and border in Firefox 3+. */
button::-moz-focus-inner, input::-moz-focus-inner { border: 0; padding: 0; }

/** 1. Remove default vertical scrollbar in IE 6/7/8/9. 2. Improve readability and alignment in all browsers. */
textarea { overflow: auto; /* 1 */ vertical-align: top; }

/* 2 */
/* ========================================================================== Tables ========================================================================== */
/** Remove most spacing between table cells. */
table { border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0; }

/* Visual Studio-like style based on original C# coloring by Jason Diamond <jason@diamond.name> */
.hljs { display: inline-block; padding: 0.5em; background: white; color: black; }

<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
	<title>ListenerFunction | tp-events</title>
	<meta name="description" content="">

	<style type="text/css">/*! normalize.css v1.1.3 | MIT License | git.io/normalize */
/* ========================================================================== HTML5 display definitions ========================================================================== */
/** Correct `block` display not defined in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. */
article, aside, details, figcaption, figure, footer, header, hgroup, main, nav, section, summary { display: block; }

/** Correct `inline-block` display not defined in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. */
audio, canvas, video { display: inline-block; *display: inline; *zoom: 1; }

/** Prevent modern browsers from displaying `audio` without controls. Remove excess height in iOS 5 devices. */
audio:not([controls]) { display: none; height: 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 7/8/9, Firefox 3, and Safari 4. Known issue: no IE 6 support. */
[hidden] { display: none; }

/* ========================================================================== Base ========================================================================== */
/** 1. Correct text resizing oddly in IE 6/7 when body `font-size` is set using `em` units. 2. Prevent iOS text size adjust after orientation change, without disabling user zoom. */
html { font-size: 100%; /* 1 */ -ms-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* 2 */ -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* 2 */ font-family: sans-serif; }

/** Address `font-family` inconsistency between `textarea` and other form elements. */
button, input, select, textarea { font-family: sans-serif; }

/** Address margins handled incorrectly in IE 6/7. */
body { margin: 0; }

/* ========================================================================== Links ========================================================================== */
/** Address `outline` inconsistency between Chrome and other browsers. */
a:focus { outline: thin dotted; }
a:active, a:hover { outline: 0; }

/** Improve readability when focused and also mouse hovered in all browsers. */
/* ========================================================================== Typography ========================================================================== */
/** Address font sizes and margins set differently in IE 6/7. Address font sizes within `section` and `article` in Firefox 4+, Safari 5, and Chrome. */
h1 { font-size: 2em; margin: 0.67em 0; }

h2 { font-size: 1.5em; margin: 0.83em 0; }

h3 { font-size: 1.17em; margin: 1em 0; }

h4, .tsd-index-panel h3 { font-size: 1em; margin: 1.33em 0; }

h5 { font-size: 0.83em; margin: 1.67em 0; }

h6 { font-size: 0.67em; margin: 2.33em 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 7/8/9, Safari 5, and Chrome. */
abbr[title] { border-bottom: 1px dotted; }

/** Address style set to `bolder` in Firefox 3+, Safari 4/5, and Chrome. */
b, strong { font-weight: bold; }

blockquote { margin: 1em 40px; }

/** Address styling not present in Safari 5 and Chrome. */
dfn { font-style: italic; }

/** Address differences between Firefox and other browsers. Known issue: no IE 6/7 normalization. */
hr { box-sizing: content-box; height: 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 6/7/8/9. */
mark { background: #ff0; color: #000; }

/** Address margins set differently in IE 6/7. */
p, pre { margin: 1em 0; }

/** Correct font family set oddly in IE 6, Safari 4/5, and Chrome. */
code, kbd, pre, samp { font-family: monospace, serif; _font-family: "courier new", monospace; font-size: 1em; }

/** Improve readability of pre-formatted text in all browsers. */
pre { white-space: pre; white-space: pre-wrap; word-wrap: break-word; }

/** Address CSS quotes not supported in IE 6/7. */
q { quotes: none; }
q:before, q:after { content: ""; content: none; }

/** Address `quotes` property not supported in Safari 4. */
/** Address inconsistent and variable font size in all browsers. */
small { font-size: 80%; }

/** Prevent `sub` and `sup` affecting `line-height` in all browsers. */
sub { font-size: 75%; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; }

sup { font-size: 75%; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; }

sub { bottom: -0.25em; }

/* ========================================================================== Lists ========================================================================== */
/** Address margins set differently in IE 6/7. */
dl, menu, ol, ul { margin: 1em 0; }

dd { margin: 0 0 0 40px; }

/** Address paddings set differently in IE 6/7. */
menu, ol, ul { padding: 0 0 0 40px; }

/** Correct list images handled incorrectly in IE 7. */
nav ul, nav ol { list-style: none; list-style-image: none; }

/* ========================================================================== Embedded content ========================================================================== */
/** 1. Remove border when inside `a` element in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. 2. Improve image quality when scaled in IE 7. */
img { border: 0; /* 1 */ -ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; }

/* 2 */
/** Correct overflow displayed oddly in IE 9. */
svg:not(:root) { overflow: hidden; }

/* ========================================================================== Figures ========================================================================== */
/** Address margin not present in IE 6/7/8/9, Safari 5, and Opera 11. */
figure, form { margin: 0; }

/* ========================================================================== Forms ========================================================================== */
/** Correct margin displayed oddly in IE 6/7. */
/** Define consistent border, margin, and padding. */
fieldset { border: 1px solid #c0c0c0; margin: 0 2px; padding: 0.35em 0.625em 0.75em; }

/** 1. Correct color not being inherited in IE 6/7/8/9. 2. Correct text not wrapping in Firefox 3. 3. Correct alignment displayed oddly in IE 6/7. */
legend { border: 0; /* 1 */ padding: 0; white-space: normal; /* 2 */ *margin-left: -7px; }

/* 3 */
/** 1. Correct font size not being inherited in all browsers. 2. Address margins set differently in IE 6/7, Firefox 3+, Safari 5, and Chrome. 3. Improve appearance and consistency in all browsers. */
button, input, select, textarea { font-size: 100%; /* 1 */ margin: 0; /* 2 */ vertical-align: baseline; /* 3 */ *vertical-align: middle; }

/* 3 */
/** Address Firefox 3+ setting `line-height` on `input` using `!important` in the UA stylesheet. */
button, input { line-height: normal; }

/** Address inconsistent `text-transform` inheritance for `button` and `select`. All other form control elements do not inherit `text-transform` values. Correct `button` style inheritance in Chrome, Safari 5+, and IE 6+. Correct `select` style inheritance in Firefox 4+ and Opera. */
button, select { text-transform: none; }

/** 1. Avoid the WebKit bug in Android 4.0.* where (2) destroys native `audio` and `video` controls. 2. Correct inability to style clickable `input` types in iOS. 3. Improve usability and consistency of cursor style between image-type `input` and others. 4. Remove inner spacing in IE 7 without affecting normal text inputs. Known issue: inner spacing remains in IE 6. */
button, html input[type="button"] { -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */ cursor: pointer; /* 3 */ *overflow: visible; }

/* 4 */
input[type="reset"], input[type="submit"] { -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */ cursor: pointer; /* 3 */ *overflow: visible; }

/* 4 */
/** Re-set default cursor for disabled elements. */
button[disabled], html input[disabled] { cursor: default; }

/** 1. Address box sizing set to content-box in IE 8/9. 2. Remove excess padding in IE 8/9. 3. Remove excess padding in IE 7. Known issue: excess padding remains in IE 6. */
input { /* 3 */ }
input[type="checkbox"], input[type="radio"] { box-sizing: border-box; /* 1 */ padding: 0; /* 2 */ *height: 13px; /* 3 */ *width: 13px; }
input[type="search"] { -webkit-appearance: textfield; /* 1 */ /* 2 */ box-sizing: content-box; }
input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-cancel-button, input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-decoration { -webkit-appearance: none; }

/** 1. Address `appearance` set to `searchfield` in Safari 5 and Chrome. 2. Address `box-sizing` set to `border-box` in Safari 5 and Chrome (include `-moz` to future-proof). */
/** Remove inner padding and search cancel button in Safari 5 and Chrome on OS X. */
/** Remove inner padding and border in Firefox 3+. */
button::-moz-focus-inner, input::-moz-focus-inner { border: 0; padding: 0; }

/** 1. Remove default vertical scrollbar in IE 6/7/8/9. 2. Improve readability and alignment in all browsers. */
textarea { overflow: auto; /* 1 */ vertical-align: top; }

/* 2 */
/* ========================================================================== Tables ========================================================================== */
/** Remove most spacing between table cells. */
table { border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0; }

/workspaces/BuyBacking/apps/web/node_modules/tp-events/dist/docs/interfaces/events.html

<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
	<title>Events | tp-events</title>
	<meta name="description" content="">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
	<style type="text/css">/*! normalize.css v1.1.3 | MIT License | git.io/normalize */
/* ========================================================================== HTML5 display definitions ========================================================================== */
/** Correct `block` display not defined in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. */
article, aside, details, figcaption, figure, footer, header, hgroup, main, nav, section, summary { display: block; }

/** Correct `inline-block` display not defined in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. */
audio, canvas, video { display: inline-block; *display: inline; *zoom: 1; }

/** Prevent modern browsers from displaying `audio` without controls. Remove excess height in iOS 5 devices. */
audio:not([controls]) { display: none; height: 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 7/8/9, Firefox 3, and Safari 4. Known issue: no IE 6 support. */
[hidden] { display: none; }

/* ========================================================================== Base ========================================================================== */
/** 1. Correct text resizing oddly in IE 6/7 when body `font-size` is set using `em` units. 2. Prevent iOS text size adjust after orientation change, without disabling user zoom. */
html { font-size: 100%; /* 1 */ -ms-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* 2 */ -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* 2 */ font-family: sans-serif; }

/** Address `font-family` inconsistency between `textarea` and other form elements. */
button, input, select, textarea { font-family: sans-serif; }

/** Address margins handled incorrectly in IE 6/7. */
body { margin: 0; }

/* ========================================================================== Links ========================================================================== */
/** Address `outline` inconsistency between Chrome and other browsers. */
a:focus { outline: thin dotted; }
a:active, a:hover { outline: 0; }

/** Improve readability when focused and also mouse hovered in all browsers. */
/* ========================================================================== Typography ========================================================================== */
/** Address font sizes and margins set differently in IE 6/7. Address font sizes within `section` and `article` in Firefox 4+, Safari 5, and Chrome. */
h1 { font-size: 2em; margin: 0.67em 0; }

h2 { font-size: 1.5em; margin: 0.83em 0; }

h3 { font-size: 1.17em; margin: 1em 0; }

h4, .tsd-index-panel h3 { font-size: 1em; margin: 1.33em 0; }

h5 { font-size: 0.83em; margin: 1.67em 0; }

h6 { font-size: 0.67em; margin: 2.33em 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 7/8/9, Safari 5, and Chrome. */
abbr[title] { border-bottom: 1px dotted; }

/** Address style set to `bolder` in Firefox 3+, Safari 4/5, and Chrome. */
b, strong { font-weight: bold; }

blockquote { margin: 1em 40px; }

/** Address styling not present in Safari 5 and Chrome. */
dfn { font-style: italic; }

/** Address differences between Firefox and other browsers. Known issue: no IE 6/7 normalization. */
hr { box-sizing: content-box; height: 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 6/7/8/9. */
mark { background: #ff0; color: #000; }

/** Address margins set differently in IE 6/7. */
p, pre { margin: 1em 0; }

/** Correct font family set oddly in IE 6, Safari 4/5, and Chrome. */
code, kbd, pre, samp { font-family: monospace, serif; _font-family: "courier new", monospace; font-size: 1em; }

/** Improve readability of pre-formatted text in all browsers. */
pre { white-space: pre; white-space: pre-wrap; word-wrap: break-word; }

/** Address CSS quotes not supported in IE 6/7. */
q { quotes: none; }
q:before, q:after { content: ""; content: none; }

/** Address `quotes` property not supported in Safari 4. */
/** Address inconsistent and variable font size in all browsers. */
small { font-size: 80%; }

/** Prevent `sub` and `sup` affecting `line-height` in all browsers. */
sub { font-size: 75%; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; }

sup { font-size: 75%; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; }

sub { bottom: -0.25em; }

/* ========================================================================== Lists ========================================================================== */
/** Address margins set differently in IE 6/7. */
dl, menu, ol, ul { margin: 1em 0; }

dd { margin: 0 0 0 40px; }

/** Address paddings set differently in IE 6/7. */
menu, ol, ul { padding: 0 0 0 40px; }

/** Correct list images handled incorrectly in IE 7. */
nav ul, nav ol { list-style: none; list-style-image: none; }

/* ========================================================================== Embedded content ========================================================================== */
/** 1. Remove border when inside `a` element in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. 2. Improve image quality when scaled in IE 7. */
img { border: 0; /* 1 */ -ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; }

/* 2 */
/** Correct overflow displayed oddly in IE 9. */
svg:not(:root) { overflow: hidden; }

/* ========================================================================== Figures ========================================================================== */
/** Address margin not present in IE 6/7/8/9, Safari 5, and Opera 11. */
figure, form { margin: 0; }

/* ========================================================================== Forms ========================================================================== */
/** Correct margin displayed oddly in IE 6/7. */
/** Define consistent border, margin, and padding. */
fieldset { border: 1px solid #c0c0c0; margin: 0 2px; padding: 0.35em 0.625em 0.75em; }

/** 1. Correct color not being inherited in IE 6/7/8/9. 2. Correct text not wrapping in Firefox 3. 3. Correct alignment displayed oddly in IE 6/7. */
legend { border: 0; /* 1 */ padding: 0; white-space: normal; /* 2 */ *margin-left: -7px; }

/* 3 */
/** 1. Correct font size not being inherited in all browsers. 2. Address margins set differently in IE 6/7, Firefox 3+, Safari 5, and Chrome. 3. Improve appearance and consistency in all browsers. */
button, input, select, textarea { font-size: 100%; /* 1 */ margin: 0; /* 2 */ vertical-align: baseline; /* 3 */ *vertical-align: middle; }

/* 3 */
/** Address Firefox 3+ setting `line-height` on `input` using `!important` in the UA stylesheet. */
button, input { line-height: normal; }

/** Address inconsistent `text-transform` inheritance for `button` and `select`. All other form control elements do not inherit `text-transform` values. Correct `button` style inheritance in Chrome, Safari 5+, and IE 6+. Correct `select` style inheritance in Firefox 4+ and Opera. */
button, select { text-transform: none; }

/** 1. Avoid the WebKit bug in Android 4.0.* where (2) destroys native `audio` and `video` controls. 2. Correct inability to style clickable `input` types in iOS. 3. Improve usability and consistency of cursor style between image-type `input` and others. 4. Remove inner spacing in IE 7 without affecting normal text inputs. Known issue: inner spacing remains in IE 6. */
button, html input[type="button"] { -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */ cursor: pointer; /* 3 */ *overflow: visible; }

/* 4 */
input[type="reset"], input[type="submit"] { -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */ cursor: pointer; /* 3 */ *overflow: visible; }

/* 4 */
/** Re-set default cursor for disabled elements. */
button[disabled], html input[disabled] { cursor: default; }

/** 1. Address box sizing set to content-box in IE 8/9. 2. Remove excess padding in IE 8/9. 3. Remove excess padding in IE 7. Known issue: excess padding remains in IE 6. */
input { /* 3 */ }
input[type="checkbox"], input[type="radio"] { box-sizing: border-box; /* 1 */ padding: 0; /* 2 */ *height: 13px; /* 3 */ *width: 13px; }
input[type="search"] { -webkit-appearance: textfield; /* 1 */ /* 2 */ box-sizing: content-box; }
input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-cancel-button, input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-decoration { -webkit-appearance: none; }

/** 1. Address `appearance` set to `searchfield` in Safari 5 and Chrome. 2. Address `box-sizing` set to `border-box` in Safari 5 and Chrome (include `-moz` to future-proof). */
/** Remove inner padding and search cancel button in Safari 5 and Chrome on OS X. */
/** Remove inner padding and border in Firefox 3+. */
button::-moz-focus-inner, input::-moz-focus-inner { border: 0; padding: 0; }

/** 1. Remove default vertical scrollbar in IE 6/7/8/9. 2. Improve readability and alignment in all browsers. */
textarea { overflow: auto; /* 1 */ vertical-align: top; }

/* 2 */
/* ========================================================================== Tables ========================================================================== */
/** Remove most spacing between table cells. */
table { border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0; }

  to { opacity: 1; } }

  to { opacity: 1; } }
@-webkit-keyframes fade-out { from { opacity: 1; visibility: visible; }
  to { opacity: 0; } }
@keyframes fade-out { from { opacity: 1; visibility: visible; }
  to { opacity: 0; } }
@-webkit-keyframes fade-in-delayed { 0% { opacity: 0; }
  33% { opacity: 0; }
  100% { opacity: 1; } }
@keyframes fade-in-delayed { 0% { opacity: 0; }
  33% { opacity: 0; }
  100% { opacity: 1; } }
@-webkit-keyframes fade-out-delayed { 0% { opacity: 1; visibility: visible; }
  66% { opacity: 0; }
  100% { opacity: 0; } }
@keyframes fade-out-delayed { 0% { opacity: 1; visibility: visible; }
  66% { opacity: 0; }
  100% { opacity: 0; } }
@-webkit-keyframes shift-to-left { from { -webkit-transform: translate(0, 0); transform: translate(0, 0); }
  to { -webkit-transform: translate(-25%, 0); transform: translate(-25%, 0); } }
@keyframes shift-to-left { from { -webkit-transform: translate(0, 0); transform: translate(0, 0); }
  to { -webkit-transform: translate(-25%, 0); transform: translate(-25%, 0); } }
@-webkit-keyframes unshift-to-left { from { -webkit-transform: translate(-25%, 0); transform: translate(-25%, 0); }
  to { -webkit-transform: translate(0, 0); transform: translate(0, 0); } }
@keyframes unshift-to-left { from { -webkit-transform: translate(-25%, 0); transform: translate(-25%, 0); }
  to { -webkit-transform: translate(0, 0); transform: translate(0, 0); } }
@-webkit-keyframes pop-in-from-right { from { -webkit-transform: translate(100%, 0); transform: translate(100%, 0); }
  to { -webkit-transform: translate(0, 0); transform: translate(0, 0); } }
@keyframes pop-in-from-right { from { -webkit-transform: translate(100%, 0); transform: translate(100%, 0); }
  to { -webkit-transform: translate(0, 0); transform: translate(0, 0); } }
@-webkit-keyframes pop-out-to-right { from { -webkit-transform: translate(0, 0); transform: translate(0, 0); visibility: visible; }
  to { -webkit-transform: translate(100%, 0); transform: translate(100%, 0); } }
@keyframes pop-out-to-right { from { -webkit-transform: translate(0, 0); transform: translate(0, 0); visibility: visible; }
  to { -webkit-transform: translate(100%, 0); transform: translate(100%, 0); } }

a { color: #4da6ff; text-decoration: none; }
a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

pre { padding: 10px; }
pre code { padding: 0; font-size: 100%; background-color: transparent; }

.tsd-typography ul { list-style: square; padding: 0 0 0 20px; margin: 0; }

.tsd-typography h5, .tsd-typography h6 { font-weight: normal; }

/workspaces/BuyBacking/apps/web/node_modules/tp-events/dist/docs/globals.html

<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
	<title>tp-events | tp-events</title>
	<meta name="description" content="">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
	<style type="text/css">/*! normalize.css v1.1.3 | MIT License | git.io/normalize */
/* ========================================================================== HTML5 display definitions ========================================================================== */
/** Correct `block` display not defined in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. */
article, aside, details, figcaption, figure, footer, header, hgroup, main, nav, section, summary { display: block; }

/** Correct `inline-block` display not defined in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. */
audio, canvas, video { display: inline-block; *display: inline; *zoom: 1; }

/** Prevent modern browsers from displaying `audio` without controls. Remove excess height in iOS 5 devices. */
audio:not([controls]) { display: none; height: 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 7/8/9, Firefox 3, and Safari 4. Known issue: no IE 6 support. */
[hidden] { display: none; }

/* ========================================================================== Base ========================================================================== */
/** 1. Correct text resizing oddly in IE 6/7 when body `font-size` is set using `em` units. 2. Prevent iOS text size adjust after orientation change, without disabling user zoom. */
html { font-size: 100%; /* 1 */ -ms-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* 2 */ -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* 2 */ font-family: sans-serif; }

/** Address `font-family` inconsistency between `textarea` and other form elements. */
button, input, select, textarea { font-family: sans-serif; }

/** Address margins handled incorrectly in IE 6/7. */
body { margin: 0; }

/* ========================================================================== Links ========================================================================== */
/** Address `outline` inconsistency between Chrome and other browsers. */
a:focus { outline: thin dotted; }
a:active, a:hover { outline: 0; }

/** Improve readability when focused and also mouse hovered in all browsers. */
/* ========================================================================== Typography ========================================================================== */
/** Address font sizes and margins set differently in IE 6/7. Address font sizes within `section` and `article` in Firefox 4+, Safari 5, and Chrome. */
h1 { font-size: 2em; margin: 0.67em 0; }

h2 { font-size: 1.5em; margin: 0.83em 0; }

h3 { font-size: 1.17em; margin: 1em 0; }

h4, .tsd-index-panel h3 { font-size: 1em; margin: 1.33em 0; }

h5 { font-size: 0.83em; margin: 1.67em 0; }

h6 { font-size: 0.67em; margin: 2.33em 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 7/8/9, Safari 5, and Chrome. */
abbr[title] { border-bottom: 1px dotted; }

/** Address style set to `bolder` in Firefox 3+, Safari 4/5, and Chrome. */
b, strong { font-weight: bold; }

blockquote { margin: 1em 40px; }

/** Address styling not present in Safari 5 and Chrome. */
dfn { font-style: italic; }

/** Address differences between Firefox and other browsers. Known issue: no IE 6/7 normalization. */
hr { box-sizing: content-box; height: 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 6/7/8/9. */
mark { background: #ff0; color: #000; }

/** Address margins set differently in IE 6/7. */
p, pre { margin: 1em 0; }

/** Correct font family set oddly in IE 6, Safari 4/5, and Chrome. */
code, kbd, pre, samp { font-family: monospace, serif; _font-family: "courier new", monospace; font-size: 1em; }

/** Improve readability of pre-formatted text in all browsers. */
pre { white-space: pre; white-space: pre-wrap; word-wrap: break-word; }

/** Address CSS quotes not supported in IE 6/7. */
q { quotes: none; }
q:before, q:after { content: ""; content: none; }

/** Address `quotes` property not supported in Safari 4. */
/** Address inconsistent and variable font size in all browsers. */
small { font-size: 80%; }

/** Prevent `sub` and `sup` affecting `line-height` in all browsers. */
sub { font-size: 75%; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; }

sup { font-size: 75%; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; }

sub { bottom: -0.25em; }

/* ========================================================================== Lists ========================================================================== */
/** Address margins set differently in IE 6/7. */
dl, menu, ol, ul { margin: 1em 0; }

dd { margin: 0 0 0 40px; }

/** Address paddings set differently in IE 6/7. */
menu, ol, ul { padding: 0 0 0 40px; }

/** Correct list images handled incorrectly in IE 7. */
nav ul, nav ol { list-style: none; list-style-image: none; }

/* ========================================================================== Embedded content ========================================================================== */
/** 1. Remove border when inside `a` element in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. 2. Improve image quality when scaled in IE 7. */
img { border: 0; /* 1 */ -ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; }

/* 2 */
/** Correct overflow displayed oddly in IE 9. */
svg:not(:root) { overflow: hidden; }

/* ========================================================================== Figures ========================================================================== */
/** Address margin not present in IE 6/7/8/9, Safari 5, and Opera 11. */
figure, form { margin: 0; }

/* ========================================================================== Forms ========================================================================== */
/** Correct margin displayed oddly in IE 6/7. */
/** Define consistent border, margin, and padding. */
fieldset { border: 1px solid #c0c0c0; margin: 0 2px; padding: 0.35em 0.625em 0.75em; }

/** 1. Correct color not being inherited in IE 6/7/8/9. 2. Correct text not wrapping in Firefox 3. 3. Correct alignment displayed oddly in IE 6/7. */
legend { border: 0; /* 1 */ padding: 0; white-space: normal; /* 2 */ *margin-left: -7px; }

/* 3 */
/** 1. Correct font size not being inherited in all browsers. 2. Address margins set differently in IE 6/7, Firefox 3+, Safari 5, and Chrome. 3. Improve appearance and consistency in all browsers. */
button, input, select, textarea { font-size: 100%; /* 1 */ margin: 0; /* 2 */ vertical-align: baseline; /* 3 */ *vertical-align: middle; }

/* 3 */
/** Address Firefox 3+ setting `line-height` on `input` using `!important` in the UA stylesheet. */
button, input { line-height: normal; }

/** Address inconsistent `text-transform` inheritance for `button` and `select`. All other form control elements do not inherit `text-transform` values. Correct `button` style inheritance in Chrome, Safari 5+, and IE 6+. Correct `select` style inheritance in Firefox 4+ and Opera. */
button, select { text-transform: none; }

/** 1. Avoid the WebKit bug in Android 4.0.* where (2) destroys native `audio` and `video` controls. 2. Correct inability to style clickable `input` types in iOS. 3. Improve usability and consistency of cursor style between image-type `input` and others. 4. Remove inner spacing in IE 7 without affecting normal text inputs. Known issue: inner spacing remains in IE 6. */
button, html input[type="button"] { -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */ cursor: pointer; /* 3 */ *overflow: visible; }

/* 4 */
input[type="reset"], input[type="submit"] { -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */ cursor: pointer; /* 3 */ *overflow: visible; }

/* 4 */
/** Re-set default cursor for disabled elements. */
button[disabled], html input[disabled] { cursor: default; }

/** 1. Address box sizing set to content-box in IE 8/9. 2. Remove excess padding in IE 8/9. 3. Remove excess padding in IE 7. Known issue: excess padding remains in IE 6. */
input { /* 3 */ }
input[type="checkbox"], input[type="radio"] { box-sizing: border-box; /* 1 */ padding: 0; /* 2 */ *height: 13px; /* 3 */ *width: 13px; }
input[type="search"] { -webkit-appearance: textfield; /* 1 */ /* 2 */ box-sizing: content-box; }
input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-cancel-button, input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-decoration { -webkit-appearance: none; }

/** 1. Address `appearance` set to `searchfield` in Safari 5 and Chrome. 2. Address `box-sizing` set to `border-box` in Safari 5 and Chrome (include `-moz` to future-proof). */
/** Remove inner padding and search cancel button in Safari 5 and Chrome on OS X. */
/** Remove inner padding and border in Firefox 3+. */
button::-moz-focus-inner, input::-moz-focus-inner { border: 0; padding: 0; }

/** 1. Remove default vertical scrollbar in IE 6/7/8/9. 2. Improve readability and alignment in all browsers. */
textarea { overflow: auto; /* 1 */ vertical-align: top; }

/* 2 */
/* ========================================================================== Tables ========================================================================== */
/** Remove most spacing between table cells. */
table { border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0; }

.no-transition { transition: none !important; }

@-webkit-keyframes fade-in { from { opacity: 0; }
  to { opacity: 1; } }

@keyframes fade-in { from { opacity: 0; }
  to { opacity: 1; } }
@-webkit-keyframes fade-out { from { opacity: 1; visibility: visible; }
  to { opacity: 0; } }
@keyframes fade-out { from { opacity: 1; visibility: visible; }
  to { opacity: 0; } }
@-webkit-keyframes fade-in-delayed { 0% { opacity: 0; }
  33% { opacity: 0; }
  100% { opacity: 1; } }
@keyframes fade-in-delayed { 0% { opacity: 0; }
  33% { opacity: 0; }
  100% { opacity: 1; } }

  66% { opacity: 0; }
  100% { opacity: 0; } }

  66% { opacity: 0; }
  100% { opacity: 0; } }

  to { -webkit-transform: translate(-25%, 0); transform: translate(-25%, 0); } }

  to { -webkit-transform: translate(0, 0); transform: translate(0, 0); } }

/* ========================================================================== HTML5 display definitions ========================================================================== */
/** Correct `block` display not defined in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. */
article, aside, details, figcaption, figure, footer, header, hgroup, main, nav, section, summary { display: block; }

/** Correct `inline-block` display not defined in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. */
audio, canvas, video { display: inline-block; *display: inline; *zoom: 1; }

/** Prevent modern browsers from displaying `audio` without controls. Remove excess height in iOS 5 devices. */
audio:not([controls]) { display: none; height: 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 7/8/9, Firefox 3, and Safari 4. Known issue: no IE 6 support. */
[hidden] { display: none; }

/* ========================================================================== Base ========================================================================== */
/** 1. Correct text resizing oddly in IE 6/7 when body `font-size` is set using `em` units. 2. Prevent iOS text size adjust after orientation change, without disabling user zoom. */
html { font-size: 100%; /* 1 */ -ms-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* 2 */ -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* 2 */ font-family: sans-serif; }

/** Address `font-family` inconsistency between `textarea` and other form elements. */
button, input, select, textarea { font-family: sans-serif; }

/** Address margins handled incorrectly in IE 6/7. */
body { margin: 0; }

/* ========================================================================== Links ========================================================================== */
/** Address `outline` inconsistency between Chrome and other browsers. */
a:focus { outline: thin dotted; }
a:active, a:hover { outline: 0; }

/** Improve readability when focused and also mouse hovered in all browsers. */
/* ========================================================================== Typography ========================================================================== */
/** Address font sizes and margins set differently in IE 6/7. Address font sizes within `section` and `article` in Firefox 4+, Safari 5, and Chrome. */
h1 { font-size: 2em; margin: 0.67em 0; }

h2 { font-size: 1.5em; margin: 0.83em 0; }

h3 { font-size: 1.17em; margin: 1em 0; }

h4, .tsd-index-panel h3 { font-size: 1em; margin: 1.33em 0; }

h5 { font-size: 0.83em; margin: 1.67em 0; }

h6 { font-size: 0.67em; margin: 2.33em 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 7/8/9, Safari 5, and Chrome. */
abbr[title] { border-bottom: 1px dotted; }

/** Address style set to `bolder` in Firefox 3+, Safari 4/5, and Chrome. */
b, strong { font-weight: bold; }

blockquote { margin: 1em 40px; }

/** Address styling not present in Safari 5 and Chrome. */
dfn { font-style: italic; }

/** Address differences between Firefox and other browsers. Known issue: no IE 6/7 normalization. */
hr { box-sizing: content-box; height: 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 6/7/8/9. */
mark { background: #ff0; color: #000; }

/** Address margins set differently in IE 6/7. */
p, pre { margin: 1em 0; }

/** Correct font family set oddly in IE 6, Safari 4/5, and Chrome. */
code, kbd, pre, samp { font-family: monospace, serif; _font-family: "courier new", monospace; font-size: 1em; }

/** Improve readability of pre-formatted text in all browsers. */
pre { white-space: pre; white-space: pre-wrap; word-wrap: break-word; }

/** Address CSS quotes not supported in IE 6/7. */
q { quotes: none; }
q:before, q:after { content: ""; content: none; }

/** Address `quotes` property not supported in Safari 4. */
/** Address inconsistent and variable font size in all browsers. */
small { font-size: 80%; }

/** Prevent `sub` and `sup` affecting `line-height` in all browsers. */
sub { font-size: 75%; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; }

sup { font-size: 75%; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; }

sub { bottom: -0.25em; }

/* ========================================================================== Lists ========================================================================== */
/** Address margins set differently in IE 6/7. */
dl, menu, ol, ul { margin: 1em 0; }

dd { margin: 0 0 0 40px; }

/** Address paddings set differently in IE 6/7. */
menu, ol, ul { padding: 0 0 0 40px; }

/** Correct list images handled incorrectly in IE 7. */
nav ul, nav ol { list-style: none; list-style-image: none; }

/* ========================================================================== Embedded content ========================================================================== */
/** 1. Remove border when inside `a` element in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. 2. Improve image quality when scaled in IE 7. */
img { border: 0; /* 1 */ -ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; }

/* 2 */
/** Correct overflow displayed oddly in IE 9. */
svg:not(:root) { overflow: hidden; }

/* ========================================================================== Figures ========================================================================== */
/** Address margin not present in IE 6/7/8/9, Safari 5, and Opera 11. */
figure, form { margin: 0; }

/* ========================================================================== Forms ========================================================================== */
/** Correct margin displayed oddly in IE 6/7. */
/** Define consistent border, margin, and padding. */
fieldset { border: 1px solid #c0c0c0; margin: 0 2px; padding: 0.35em 0.625em 0.75em; }

/** 1. Correct color not being inherited in IE 6/7/8/9. 2. Correct text not wrapping in Firefox 3. 3. Correct alignment displayed oddly in IE 6/7. */
legend { border: 0; /* 1 */ padding: 0; white-space: normal; /* 2 */ *margin-left: -7px; }

/* 3 */
/** 1. Correct font size not being inherited in all browsers. 2. Address margins set differently in IE 6/7, Firefox 3+, Safari 5, and Chrome. 3. Improve appearance and consistency in all browsers. */
button, input, select, textarea { font-size: 100%; /* 1 */ margin: 0; /* 2 */ vertical-align: baseline; /* 3 */ *vertical-align: middle; }

/* 3 */
/** Address Firefox 3+ setting `line-height` on `input` using `!important` in the UA stylesheet. */
button, input { line-height: normal; }

/** Address inconsistent `text-transform` inheritance for `button` and `select`. All other form control elements do not inherit `text-transform` values. Correct `button` style inheritance in Chrome, Safari 5+, and IE 6+. Correct `select` style inheritance in Firefox 4+ and Opera. */
button, select { text-transform: none; }

/** 1. Avoid the WebKit bug in Android 4.0.* where (2) destroys native `audio` and `video` controls. 2. Correct inability to style clickable `input` types in iOS. 3. Improve usability and consistency of cursor style between image-type `input` and others. 4. Remove inner spacing in IE 7 without affecting normal text inputs. Known issue: inner spacing remains in IE 6. */
button, html input[type="button"] { -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */ cursor: pointer; /* 3 */ *overflow: visible; }

/* 4 */
input[type="reset"], input[type="submit"] { -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */ cursor: pointer; /* 3 */ *overflow: visible; }

/* 4 */
/** Re-set default cursor for disabled elements. */
button[disabled], html input[disabled] { cursor: default; }

/** 1. Address box sizing set to content-box in IE 8/9. 2. Remove excess padding in IE 8/9. 3. Remove excess padding in IE 7. Known issue: excess padding remains in IE 6. */
input { /* 3 */ }
input[type="checkbox"], input[type="radio"] { box-sizing: border-box; /* 1 */ padding: 0; /* 2 */ *height: 13px; /* 3 */ *width: 13px; }
input[type="search"] { -webkit-appearance: textfield; /* 1 */ /* 2 */ box-sizing: content-box; }
input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-cancel-button, input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-decoration { -webkit-appearance: none; }

/** 1. Address `appearance` set to `searchfield` in Safari 5 and Chrome. 2. Address `box-sizing` set to `border-box` in Safari 5 and Chrome (include `-moz` to future-proof). */
/** Remove inner padding and search cancel button in Safari 5 and Chrome on OS X. */
/** Remove inner padding and border in Firefox 3+. */
button::-moz-focus-inner, input::-moz-focus-inner { border: 0; padding: 0; }

/** 1. Remove default vertical scrollbar in IE 6/7/8/9. 2. Improve readability and alignment in all browsers. */
textarea { overflow: auto; /* 1 */ vertical-align: top; }

/* 2 */
/* ========================================================================== Tables ========================================================================== */
/** Remove most spacing between table cells. */
table { border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0; }

/* Visual Studio-like style based on original C# coloring by Jason Diamond <jason@diamond.name> */

a:active,a:hover{outline:0;text-decoration:underline}

  font-size:11px;font-weight:400;margin:0}
.inset,ul.inset{margin-left:20px}
.inset{font-size:.9em}

  padding:1px 0 1px 15px;margin:1.2em 0}

<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">

	<style type="text/css">/*! normalize.css v1.1.3 | MIT License | git.io/normalize */
/* ========================================================================== HTML5 display definitions ========================================================================== */
/** Correct `block` display not defined in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. */
article, aside, details, figcaption, figure, footer, header, hgroup, main, nav, section, summary { display: block; }

/** Correct `inline-block` display not defined in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. */
audio, canvas, video { display: inline-block; *display: inline; *zoom: 1; }

/** Prevent modern browsers from displaying `audio` without controls. Remove excess height in iOS 5 devices. */
audio:not([controls]) { display: none; height: 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 7/8/9, Firefox 3, and Safari 4. Known issue: no IE 6 support. */
[hidden] { display: none; }

/* ========================================================================== Base ========================================================================== */
/** 1. Correct text resizing oddly in IE 6/7 when body `font-size` is set using `em` units. 2. Prevent iOS text size adjust after orientation change, without disabling user zoom. */
html { font-size: 100%; /* 1 */ -ms-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* 2 */ -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* 2 */ font-family: sans-serif; }

/** Address `font-family` inconsistency between `textarea` and other form elements. */
button, input, select, textarea { font-family: sans-serif; }

/** Address margins handled incorrectly in IE 6/7. */
body { margin: 0; }

/* ========================================================================== Links ========================================================================== */
/** Address `outline` inconsistency between Chrome and other browsers. */
a:focus { outline: thin dotted; }
a:active, a:hover { outline: 0; }

/** Improve readability when focused and also mouse hovered in all browsers. */
/* ========================================================================== Typography ========================================================================== */
/** Address font sizes and margins set differently in IE 6/7. Address font sizes within `section` and `article` in Firefox 4+, Safari 5, and Chrome. */
h1 { font-size: 2em; margin: 0.67em 0; }

h2 { font-size: 1.5em; margin: 0.83em 0; }

h3 { font-size: 1.17em; margin: 1em 0; }

h4, .tsd-index-panel h3 { font-size: 1em; margin: 1.33em 0; }

h5 { font-size: 0.83em; margin: 1.67em 0; }

h6 { font-size: 0.67em; margin: 2.33em 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 7/8/9, Safari 5, and Chrome. */
abbr[title] { border-bottom: 1px dotted; }

/** Address style set to `bolder` in Firefox 3+, Safari 4/5, and Chrome. */
b, strong { font-weight: bold; }

blockquote { margin: 1em 40px; }

/** Address styling not present in Safari 5 and Chrome. */
dfn { font-style: italic; }

/** Address differences between Firefox and other browsers. Known issue: no IE 6/7 normalization. */
hr { box-sizing: content-box; height: 0; }

/** Address styling not present in IE 6/7/8/9. */
mark { background: #ff0; color: #000; }

/** Address margins set differently in IE 6/7. */
p, pre { margin: 1em 0; }

/** Correct font family set oddly in IE 6, Safari 4/5, and Chrome. */
code, kbd, pre, samp { font-family: monospace, serif; _font-family: "courier new", monospace; font-size: 1em; }

/** Improve readability of pre-formatted text in all browsers. */
pre { white-space: pre; white-space: pre-wrap; word-wrap: break-word; }

/** Address CSS quotes not supported in IE 6/7. */
q { quotes: none; }
q:before, q:after { content: ""; content: none; }

/** Address `quotes` property not supported in Safari 4. */
/** Address inconsistent and variable font size in all browsers. */
small { font-size: 80%; }

/** Prevent `sub` and `sup` affecting `line-height` in all browsers. */
sub { font-size: 75%; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; }

sup { font-size: 75%; line-height: 0; position: relative; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; }

sub { bottom: -0.25em; }

/* ========================================================================== Lists ========================================================================== */
/** Address margins set differently in IE 6/7. */
dl, menu, ol, ul { margin: 1em 0; }

dd { margin: 0 0 0 40px; }

/** Address paddings set differently in IE 6/7. */
menu, ol, ul { padding: 0 0 0 40px; }

/** Correct list images handled incorrectly in IE 7. */
nav ul, nav ol { list-style: none; list-style-image: none; }

/* ========================================================================== Embedded content ========================================================================== */
/** 1. Remove border when inside `a` element in IE 6/7/8/9 and Firefox 3. 2. Improve image quality when scaled in IE 7. */
img { border: 0; /* 1 */ -ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; }

/* 2 */
/** Correct overflow displayed oddly in IE 9. */
svg:not(:root) { overflow: hidden; }

/* ========================================================================== Figures ========================================================================== */
/** Address margin not present in IE 6/7/8/9, Safari 5, and Opera 11. */
figure, form { margin: 0; }

/* ========================================================================== Forms ========================================================================== */
/** Correct margin displayed oddly in IE 6/7. */
/** Define consistent border, margin, and padding. */
fieldset { border: 1px solid #c0c0c0; margin: 0 2px; padding: 0.35em 0.625em 0.75em; }

/** 1. Correct color not being inherited in IE 6/7/8/9. 2. Correct text not wrapping in Firefox 3. 3. Correct alignment displayed oddly in IE 6/7. */
legend { border: 0; /* 1 */ padding: 0; white-space: normal; /* 2 */ *margin-left: -7px; }

/* 3 */
/** 1. Correct font size not being inherited in all browsers. 2. Address margins set differently in IE 6/7, Firefox 3+, Safari 5, and Chrome. 3. Improve appearance and consistency in all browsers. */
button, input, select, textarea { font-size: 100%; /* 1 */ margin: 0; /* 2 */ vertical-align: baseline; /* 3 */ *vertical-align: middle; }

/* 3 */
/** Address Firefox 3+ setting `line-height` on `input` using `!important` in the UA stylesheet. */
button, input { line-height: normal; }

/** Address inconsistent `text-transform` inheritance for `button` and `select`. All other form control elements do not inherit `text-transform` values. Correct `button` style inheritance in Chrome, Safari 5+, and IE 6+. Correct `select` style inheritance in Firefox 4+ and Opera. */
button, select { text-transform: none; }

/** 1. Avoid the WebKit bug in Android 4.0.* where (2) destroys native `audio` and `video` controls. 2. Correct inability to style clickable `input` types in iOS. 3. Improve usability and consistency of cursor style between image-type `input` and others. 4. Remove inner spacing in IE 7 without affecting normal text inputs. Known issue: inner spacing remains in IE 6. */
button, html input[type="button"] { -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */ cursor: pointer; /* 3 */ *overflow: visible; }

/* 4 */
input[type="reset"], input[type="submit"] { -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */ cursor: pointer; /* 3 */ *overflow: visible; }

/* 4 */
/** Re-set default cursor for disabled elements. */
button[disabled], html input[disabled] { cursor: default; }

/** 1. Address box sizing set to content-box in IE 8/9. 2. Remove excess padding in IE 8/9. 3. Remove excess padding in IE 7. Known issue: excess padding remains in IE 6. */
input { /* 3 */ }
input[type="checkbox"], input[type="radio"] { box-sizing: border-box; /* 1 */ padding: 0; /* 2 */ *height: 13px; /* 3 */ *width: 13px; }
input[type="search"] { -webkit-appearance: textfield; /* 1 */ /* 2 */ box-sizing: content-box; }
input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-cancel-button, input[type="search"]::-webkit-search-decoration { -webkit-appearance: none; }

/** 1. Address `appearance` set to `searchfield` in Safari 5 and Chrome. 2. Address `box-sizing` set to `border-box` in Safari 5 and Chrome (include `-moz` to future-proof). */
/** Remove inner padding and search cancel button in Safari 5 and Chrome on OS X. */
/** Remove inner padding and border in Firefox 3+. */
button::-moz-focus-inner, input::-moz-focus-inner { border: 0; padding: 0; }

/** 1. Remove default vertical scrollbar in IE 6/7/8/9. 2. Improve readability and alignment in all browsers. */
textarea { overflow: auto; /* 1 */ vertical-align: top; }

/* 2 */
/* ========================================================================== Tables ========================================================================== */
/** Remove most spacing between table cells. */
table { border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0; }

<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
